The paper discusses a data structure (red black trees) and a concurrency technique (flat combining) which are both commonly studied in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with distributed computing, which suggests cs.Distributed as a likely category. The use of flat combining may also relate to parallel computing, which could place the paper in cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.PF (Performance).
